At the current moment, the time tracking field like timespent can be search based on the value only. But, it does not support using the date range etc.

We discovered this while investigating on an issue in SAC. 

Basically when we run the getDocumentTitle() function in the developer console, we will get a document title which is not related to the current screen. Reviewing the code behind the function:
{code}
function () {
    if (AJS.$(".aui-popup-heading").html() != null && AJS.$(".aui-popup-heading").clone().children().remove().end().text().length > 0) {
        return jQuery.trim(AJS.$(".aui-popup-heading").clone().children().remove().end().text());
    }
    else if (AJS.$(".dialog-title").html() != null && AJS.$(".dialog-title").html().length > 0) {
        return jQuery.trim(AJS.$(".dialog-title").html());
    }
    return document.title;
}
{code}

This tells us that the function will return a dialog screen title, even if the dialog screen do not appear on the screen.

We need to ensure that the AJS.getDocumentTitle() function will only return the dialog title when the dialog screen is open.

